4.  History of low testosterone levels.  Had been previously on injections but is not currently on injections.
5.  ED.  He is not currently using the Cialis but had this prescribed previously.
6.  Coronary artery disease.  Please see Dr. Edward note from December 9, 2009, for details.
7.  Early family history of coronary artery disease.
8.  Hypertension.  This has been stable more recently.
9.  Nephrolithiasis, 2006 he had an episode and had lithotripsy.
10.  GERD.  This is stable.
11.  Anxiety.  He had issues with anxiety with his new diagnosis back in December, but he is coping better.  He was on trazodone for a short time and now is off it.
12.  Overweight.
13.  Hyperlipidemia.
PAST SURGICAL HISTORY
1.  Vasectomy.
2.  Left eye surgery after a piece of metal was in his eye.
3.  He underwent three surgeries for appendicitis in 2004.  The first surgery drains were placed, then shortly afterwards the appendectomy was performed, and then he had another surgery, and a piece of his small intestine was resected.  His appendix had burst, and an irrigation of the peritoneal cavity was performed.
4.  For left nephrolithiasis lithotripsy was performed, 2006.
5. Please see details of cardiac stent placements under PMH above.

